NUM and AMCU members, who have been on strike at Sibanye-Stillwater's gold operations since 9 March, leave after holding a mass meeting at the Driefontein mine in the southwest of Johannesburg. 22 April 2022. Reuters/Siphiwe SibekoUnder Sibanye's "final settlement offer", entry-level employees would be given an annual increase of R850 a month each year between 2022 and 2024, including a R50 increase in living out allowance.Sibanye previously offered entry-level workers an annual increase of R800 a month, including a R100-a-month increase in living out allowance. The company's offer to miners, artisans and officials remains a 5% pay increase each year.